%h1 Let's download Hackety Hack!
%p.body To kick off your download, <a href="https://github.com/downloads/hacketyhack/hacketyhack/hacketyhack-1.0.0.exe.zip">click here for Windows</a> or <a href="https://github.com/downloads/hacketyhack/hacketyhack/hacketyhack-1.0.0.dmg">here for Mac OS X 10.6</a> (On the Mac, you need a 64 bit computer. Core 2 Duo or better. 32 bit support is coming in the future.)
%p.body If you have Linux, <a href="https://github.com/downloads/hacketyhack/hacketyhack/hacketyhack-1.0.0-x86_64-linux.run">give this a shot for 64 bit</a>, or <a href="https://github.com/downloads/hacketyhack/hacketyhack/hacketyhack-1.0-1386-Linux.run">here for 32 bit Linux.</a>. Linux support is a bit experimental at the moment, so don't hesitate to <a href="mailto:steve+hackety@steveklabnik.com">give some feedback about it</a>.

%p.body I am working on supporting more platforms at the moment. If you already know how to code and you'd like to help out, please <a href="mailto:steve+hackety@steveklabnik.com">send me an email</a>, I'd love a hand.
